24/08/2003
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- NATO-led peacekeepers in Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) and Kosovo will begin a several-month operational drill on Tuesday (26 August), according to KFOR. More than 6,500 soldiers from NATO nations will participate in the annual exercise, aimed at testing the rapid reaction intervention capabilities of Alliance troops.
In other news, SFOR personnel working with members of the Republika Srpska Army found an illegal arms storage facility near Bosanska Gradiska, according to an announcement Saturday. The weapons were transferred to an SFOR depot. (AFP, PBS BiH - 23/08/03)
